                                            <h2>WHO Head Quarters</h2>

                                            <p>Department of Food Safety and Zoonoses:
                                                Philippe Verger is currently collaborating in all phases of the design of the tool.  FAO/WHO GIFT is developed in synergy with the development of FAO/WHO CIFOCOss (Chronic Individual Food Consumption – Summary Statistics) which is developed under the responsibility of Philippe Verger.
                                                Nutrition Department:
                                                Francesco Branca is regularly updated on FAO/WHO GIFT development to ensure that the tool will also help WHO in serving countries within WHO specific area of work </p>
                                        </div>


                                        <div class="swiper-slide home-event red-slide">
                                            <h2>European Food Safety Authority (EFSA)</h2>

                                            <p>Francesco Vernazza has updated the food categorization system developed by EFSA (FoodEx2) so that it can serve global purposes and be used in FAO/WHO GIFT. Advice is being sought from Davide Arcella in relation to the link with food composition data and from Stefano Cappe in relation to the dissemination platform</p>
                                        </div>

                                            <div class="swiper-slide home-event red-slide">
                                                <h2>HarvestPlus</h2>
                                                <p>Mourad Moursi has facilitated the preparation and sharing of the 4 HarvestPlus datasets that are included in the pilot FAO/WHO GIFT</p>

                                            </div>

                                            <div class="swiper-slide home-event red-slide">
                                                <h2>Tufts University – Global Dietary Database - Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation</h2>

                                                <p>Tufts University (Jennifer Coates) coordinates the INDDEX project funded by Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation. This project includes activities aimed at developing FAO/WHO GIFT. The tool is developed in synergy with the Global Dietary Database (GDD) team led by Dariush Mozaffarian (Dean of the Tufts University Friedman School of Nutrition Science & Policy) </p>
                                            </div>

